              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><h3>Annotation</h3><table class=\"hl7__eu__lab__report\"><tr><th>Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us</th></tr><tr><td>The laboratory results show an elevated HbA1c (6.0%), indicating impaired glucose metabolism or possible prediabetes/early diabetes, despite a normal fasting glucose. Renal function (urea, creatinine), electrolytes, and calcium are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation for glycemic status and consideration of further evaluation or intervention for glucose control.</td></tr></table></div>"
